So mani/ai, attacks of madness;
							qa/natoi, executions, cases of
								death.

*)aqh=nai, Athens (upper and
							lower townsSometimes explained as a locative
								mistaken for a plural (Johannson).); *qh=bai, Thebes;
							nw=ta, back;
							ste/rna, sth/qh, breast;
							pro/swpa, countenance;
							me/twpa, forehead.

The use of the plural often gives the idea of fulness (o)/gkos); cf. AR. Rhet. 3.6, Ps.- Longin.
							§ 23; hence it is often used in poetry, e. g. do/moi, apartments;
							me/gara, halls;
							ga/moi, nuptial rites;
							tafai/, sepulchre
								(burial-grounds). Compare also the poetical use of texnh/mata, texna/smata, handiwork,
							paideu/mata, nursling,
							etc., and the prose expression paidika/,
							favorite, which is used only in the plural form.

a)/mpelos, vine(yard);
							a)/rguros, silver(plate);
							h( i(/ppos, cavalry;
							h( ka/mhlos (HDT. ),
							camelry, etc.

